Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? ​Administrative Assistant for Academic Library Consortium - CORRECTION TO POSTING Calgary , AB Description The Council of Prairie and Pacific University Libraries (COPPUL) is a consortium of 22 university libraries in Manitoba, Saskatchewan, Alberta and British Columbia. Members cooperate and collaborate in areas such as digital preservation, e-resource licensing, Indigenous knowledge, scholarly communication, shared print archiving, resource sharing and more. We are seeking an Administrative Assistant with experience in academic libraries to provide high-level administrative support to the Executive Director with the day-to-day business of the organization . This is a 15 hour per week contract position reporting to the Executive Director. Tasks include scheduling meetings, preparing correspondence, planning meetings, responding to emails, and other related functions. This individual exhibits a high level of professionalism and possesses excellent written and verbal communication skills and interpersonal skills to interact with board members, COPPUL members and staff under the direction of the Executive Director. This individual is a self-starter, extremely organized and has a keen eye for detail and highly developed problem solving skills. As COPPUL is a virtual organization without a physical space in which to work, this position also requires the Administrative Assistant to work independently in a virtual environment preferably in Calgary, Alberta.Key areas of ResponsibilitiesProvides full administrative assistance to the Executive Director.Organizes logistics for in-person and virtual Directors meetings including catering, hotel and meeting room arrangements as needed.Attends board meetings and records, transcribes, and distributes meeting minutes; and maintains historical files.Updates and maintains COPPUL WordPress-based website including adding content, updating committee information, posting news stories, finding and adding images.Maintains Executive Director’s appointment calendar and manages Executive Directors schedule accordingly.Conserves Executive Director’s time by responding to routine emails; drafting letters and documents.Maintains listservs and Director, Board and member lists currently stored in excel files.Maintains and develops a procedures manual to ensure all administrative processes are documented to support succession planning. Support Executive Director with tracking financial information.Follows up with vendors and members on outstanding accounts payable and receivableSets up Board and Director meetings, and where appropriate, takes minutes.Skills/QualificationsDemonstrated ability to learn and adopt new technologies (e.g., WordPress)Highly skilled in Microsoft applications; Outlook, Word, Excel and Power PointAbility to handle confidential information with discretionEffectively communicate with Executives, Board members, members and employees.High level of organizational, time management and customer relations skills.Detail oriented, accurate and able to act autonomously with minimal supervision.Experience or knowledge of post-secondary education, academic libraries, and/or non-profits.Minimum years of experience: 2 years experience, preferably in an academic library.About COPPUL The Council of Prairie and Pacific University Libraries (COPPUL) is a non-profit library consortium that serves academic libraries in Western Canada. Staff work remotely and in some instances are seconded from their home institutions. Our mission is to identify areas of intersection across the membership. We embrace opportunities for learning, engagement, and collaboration with new and existing partners. COPPUL is committed to equity and diversity and seeks to foster the inclusion of voices that have been underrepresented or discouraged. We encourage applications from members of groups that have been marginalized on the basis of sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, racialization, ability, political belief, religion, marital or family status, age, and/or status as a First Nation, Metis, Inuit, or Indigenous person. Compensation: $30 - $33.00 hour.To apply, please send a letter of application, resume and the names of three references to Vivian Stieda, COPPUL Executive Director, at execdir@coppul.ca, by April 30, 2023. Compensation $30 - $33 per hour Closes: 30 April, 2023 Council of Prairie and Pacific University Libraries Calgary , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
