ps with management, staff, and communityCommitment to ongoing professional developmentExcellent spoken and written EnglishReasonable availability for evening and weekend shiftsCreativity, flexibility, and a strong desire to serve the community Hours of work: 35 hours/weekTo apply: please drop resume off at:Lloyd Mall, Unit 1605211 44th St. Lloydminster, ABor email csikora@lloydminster.info Compensation $70 000 - $80 000 per annum commensurate with education and experience with a generous benefits package including RRSP matching and vacation Closes: 7 May, 2023 Lloydminster Public Library Lloydminster , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
