Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Content Marketing Manager Toronto , ON Description Job Summary:Are you a fan of public libraries? Better yet, have you worked at one before?Are you passionate about storytelling and generating creative ideas?Are you an ace at understanding your audience and creating content that addresses their challenges and goals? If you answered yes to all the above, keep reading! BiblioCommons, is looking for a dynamic Content Marketing Manager to join the Marketing Team and drive brand awareness, generate and nurture leads, and boost growth through content.Job Description:As the Content Marketing Manager, you will be responsible for planning, creating, and distributing valuable and relevant content for all stages of the buyer’s journey.The successful candidate will be talented, hands-on, passionate, and most importantly, a superb storyteller that loves creating high-quality engaging content. The Content Marketing Manager will report to the Marketing Director and will work closely with the marketing, sales, and customer success teams as part of the go-to-market growth strategy.RESPONSIBILITIES (How you’ll make an impact)Own and develop highly engaging, educational, and valuable content to drive demand generation and nurture contacts at all stages of the funnelManage the strategy and creation of content for the website (blog articles, success stories, guides, reports, and more) Understand our various buyer personas and develop product positioning and messaging that resonates with themCollaborate with BiblioTeam members to create sales enablement content that will best communicate the needs of our prospects and customersCreate and optimize digital content with the best SEM and SEO practicesMaintain a content calendar that aligns with marketing initiatives, campaigns, and goalsKeep an updated content inventory that BiblioTeam members can easily reference and leverageMeasure and report on content performance and adjust as needed to exceed expectationsResearch and stay up to date on the latest content trends and public library industry topicsQUALIFICATIONS (What you’ll bring to the team)College diploma or Bachelor’s degree in marketing or related library discipline5 years of experience in content strategy, development, and productionHighly skilled storyteller that understands target audiences and how to address their needsGreat attention to detail and an exceptional writer, editor, and proof-readerUp to date with the latest trends and best practices in content marketingAbility to manage multiple projects under tight deadlines, working with a high degree of independenceOrganized! Must be diligent about providing timely project updates and managing a wide range of incoming requests and responsibilitiesStrong work ethic and collaboration skills, working with cross-functional teams to achieve a shared goalEnergetic and motivated with a positive attitude and sense of humorSelf-starter who enjoys problem-solving and the ability to learn quicklyExperience working with HubSpot, Google AnalyticsStrong understanding of SEO/SEM skillsOUR MISSION (A little about our values)Our growing staff (aka BiblioTeam and BiblioBuddies) support library staff and patrons in making the most of the BiblioCommons enterprise suite of products. Our mission is to support libraries in ensuring that the online public library experience is as welcoming and inspiring as a visit to a physical library. A lot of companies tout 'social impact', but at BiblioCommons we serve over 8 million diverse users each month by partnering with over 370 public libraries (including consortia members) in Canada, the US, New Zealand, and Australia. Libraries are more than just book stacks—they are public spaces that foster learning, connection, and community; and BiblioCommons brings that community online with clever software that powers many of the largest libraries.Find out more about our people and culture at BiblioCommons.com/CareersApply here! Compensation $80,000 - $90,000 Canadian Closes: 14 May, 2023 BiblioCommons Corp. Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
